original_review.review_text: I still wear this jacket often when it’s not too cold. It keeps me warm for the most part with just a long sleeve shirt. I like that it’s very compact and lightweight the down jacket. I happen to love the yellow colour on this jacket, it’s very robust. But it’s not for everybody. This is a good jacket for fall, autumn, maybe early winter, but this won’t keep you warm when it’s very cold like in the minus. The jacket is very light and is not meant for extreme cold temperatures. The zipper seems okay a little flimsy at times. I bought the jacket on sale so the value for the money was decent. It seems to do well when it gets wet a bit, but I don’t know how well it would do with sever raining or with thunderstorms. It seems to be a little waterproof to a certain point. Read more

original_review.review_text: First and foremost, security is paramount when traveling, and this backpack delivers with its anti-theft design. The hidden zipper closures and durable, slash-proof material offer peace of mind, allowing me to navigate crowded airports and bustling city streets worry-free. Beyond its security features, the functionality of this backpack is outstanding. The built-in USB charging port is a game-changer, keeping my devices powered up on the go. Whether it's charging my phone while waiting at the gate or topping up my tablet during a long flight, having easy access to power has been incredibly convenient. Additionally, the backpack's organization is top-notch. The well-designed compartments and pockets make it a breeze to keep everything in its place, from my laptop and tablet to my passport and travel documents. Plus, the padded laptop sleeve provides extra protection for my tech essentials, giving me peace of mind during transit. And let's talk about comfort. The padded shoulder straps and back panel ensure that even when fully loaded, this backpack remains comfortable to wear for extended periods. Whether I'm dashing through the airport or exploring a new city on foot, I never feel weighed down or uncomfortable. Overall, this carry-on travel backpack is a must-have for any traveler. Its combination of style, security, and convenience make it the ultimate travel companion. I can't recommend it highly enough! Read more

original_review.review_text: The Amazon Fire TV Stick HD is, overall, a solid streaming device with some great features, but it doesn’t come without its frustrations. The positives: The user interface is highly intuitive and very responsive -- exactly what you’d expect from an Amazon product. Navigating through menus is smooth, and the layout is simple and easy to follow, which makes using the device a breeze. Setting it up was incredibly easy as well. I was up and running in just a few minutes, with minimal hassle. Alexa integration is another plus, allowing for voice controls that make the overall experience more efficient. However, there are some minor gripes.  One of the biggest selling points is access to "free" video content, which initially sounds fantastic -- who doesn't want more free stuff?  However, the reality is a bit underwhelming. Most of the content under the free tab either isn't that appealing, or you still have to pay to unlock episodes. Youtube is included as part of the "free" but tbh, YouTube is available on almost every TV stick out there. It doesn’t really add anything special to the device. Another slight inconvenience is the frequent need to install third-party apps to access content. You think you've found something to watch, but instead, you're prompted to download and install yet another app before you can actually start streaming. It really breaks one out of s the experience of seamless browsing and watching, which is what you'd expect from a device like this. It would be much better if the content was directly available without all these additional steps. The "free" tab is more geared toward pushing paid content on me than giving me actual free stuff. Every time I browse it, I’m met with more upsells than real free viewing options. At the end of the day, this is still a decent streaming device, especially for those who already have Prime or are deeply integrated into Amazon's ecosystem. But if you're getting it with the expectation of a treasure trove of free content, you’re going to be disappointed. I would like Amazon to improve the quality and availability of truly free content. If they can address that, the Fire TV Stick would be an even stronger contender in the streaming world. Read more

original_review.review_text: Already own a sub 250 gram drone with a 4K camera and 3-axis gimble so... Did extensive research prior to purchasing the DJI Neo by reading/watching lots of reviews. After a few days toying with it, I am 110% sold. Nope by no means is it perfect yet IMHO, the positive far outweigh the negatives. Build quality is first rate in my opinion so should stand up fairly well. Props are well protected, battery latches firmly into place, has a camera guard/cover, power and mode control buttons are top mounted, has voice prompts, available in a "Fly More Combo" kit, etc. Super small footprint yet packs a punch. Multifunction in that it can be flown w/o a phone or RC controller, with a mobile phone, and/or with the DJI RC-N3 remote controller. Has palm takeoff and landing, voice control, AI subject tracking and quickshots, etc. Compared to other drones equipped with a single axis gimble, DJI stabilization technology really does a great job in keeping the footage smooth. I've gotten between 11-13 minutes of battery runtime so we are OK with that. My only real complaint(s) would have to be the limited onboard (non-removable/upgradable) storage. Although 22GB seems fairly ample so far it is an odd choice for such a device... To download footage requires plugging the drone into a device, no battery/power-on needed. Read more

original_review.review_text: Here's my take on this monitor after a few weeks of use. Pros: Cost-Effective: As price was a major factor for me, this monitor met my needs perfectly. It's affordable without sacrificing the quality Samsung is known for. Reliable Brand: Opting for Samsung was an easy choice due to their reputation for reliability. This monitor has lived up to that expectation, operating smoothly since setup. Ideal Port Orientation: Unlike many other brands, the connection ports on this Samsung monitor are oriented downwards. This design choice minimizes stress on the connectors, potentially enhancing their longevity—a subtle yet appreciated feature. Cons: Insufficient Contrast: The monitor falls short in the contrast department. For instance, when I’m on the Gmail page, it's difficult to distinguish between read and unread emails due to the lack of contrast. This can be a significant drawback for those who rely on visual cues for efficiency. Read more

original_review.review_text: This little drone is impressive. It’s so light, but very nimble, and quite fast as well There are so many ways to fly it, wether it’s just from the palm of your hand (don’t forget you will need to activate it first), or with your cellphone (it has a virtual joystick), or with the controller RCN2 or RCN3, or RC2, or with the motion controller, or with the fpv controller 3… even in manual mode with the goggles 3! It can handle winds surprisingly well, and the footage will come out surprisingly good considering. It seems like it was designed to be a selfie drone, but it can do a lot more, even in 4K 30fps or 1080 60fps No D-log or anything like that here, bu If you have a controller, you will be able to make the video a lot better by lowering the sharpness to the minimum. Small hiccup during activation, if you try to do it with an iPad, or a cellphone on wifi, it needs to be connected to the drone’s wifi network, thus disconnecting you from the internet. You need a cellphone with a cellular network and the drone’s network at the same time to get through activation. No obstacle avoidance, but it follows your path very precisely and you can have it avoid trees even in a small forest trail. Read more

original_review.review_text: I purchased this monitor for my wife’s home office and it came with no screws to mount to the stand. When contacting Samsung about the missing parts they first told me that it IS covered under the warranty and that they’ll send the two little screws free of charge. 2 days later however, they sent a random email with a different resolution, that I never agreed to. When I contacted the customer service they said that I had to pay for these 2 little screws, because I didn’t report the missing parts within 48 hours of delivery. However, we never had the opportunity to open the package for a few days because we were out of town. As much as I tried to fight this and escalate this, Samsung refuses to acknowledge their error in this and is putting the blame on us for not noticing the missing parts within their policy time, which is extremely egregious and does not give the customer enough time to notice such things (especially in our case). It is extremely disappointing as this is not the first time Samsung Customer Support has let me down like this. They’ve previously made me give back a free gift because they sent me the wrong colour phone and in order to get the correct colour that I ordered, I had to return the free gift. I can’t believe a company of this size treats their customers so poorly. We are now stuck with a wobbly monitor that could tip over at any given moment, because this billion dollar company won’t waive a $3 fee to send us parts that should’ve been provided to us in the first place. Disgusting. Read more

original_review.review_title: Muy diveridk y sencillo de usar
original_review.review_text: No es tan sencillo el inicio. Se deben seguir varios pasis en orden: 1 Cargar primero las tres baterías en el cargador. 2 Descargar el programa DJI Assistance para Windows o MacOS. Debe cuidarse que sea el que corresponde al Neo. 3 Leyendo el código QR impreso en la guía rápisa, descargar la App DJI Fly para Android o iOS. No se encuentra por medio de la tienda. Hay que descargarlo e instalarlo. 4 El firmware en el dron y en el cargador son de la versión inicial por lo que antes de hacer otra cosa se debe encender el dron, conectarlo a la computadora con el cable USB y ejecutar el DJI Assistant. De forma utomática listará las versiones disponibles. Solo hay que elegirla para que se descargue e instale. 5 Repetir el paso anterior pero conectando el control RC-N3. 6 Ahora hay que activarlo. Para ello se debe activar en el celular la localización, wifi y bluetooth. Arrancar la app DJI Fly y seguir los pasos para la activación. Si se intenta la activación con el firmware original, no funcionará. Después de todo lo anterior ya está listo para usarse. Funciona muy bien y el video es de muy buena calidad. Sorprende lo estable del vuelo y lo sencillo de su manejo. Read more

original_review.review_title: Worth Every Penny and Then Some – Absolutely Incredible!
original_review.review_text: The media could not be loaded.\n                 I have one question—how on earth is this thing less than four hundred dollars?! This is one of the best purchases I’ve ever made on a drone. It’s perfectly steady, and the camera is stunning. The quality of the footage is so clear and crisp, it’s almost unbelievable. And the range? It can go so far away that I can’t even fathom the distance. After receiving a terrible drone order that was a complete waste of money, I truly understood just how incredible the DJI Mini 2 SE is. It felt necessary to leave this review despite the fact that not many people might see it because the difference is night and day. This drone is leagues above anything else I’ve tried. Despite a few crashes, this drone works flawlessly and feels like it should be worth at least $1,500. The return-to-home feature is incredibly precise—literally down to the inch—and the motion sensors are spot-on as well. It's also ridiculously easy to fly, which is perfect for anyone, whether you're a beginner or an experienced pilot. The best part? You don’t even need to register it because it’s so lightweight. Plus, it’s super easy to bring into other countries. I packed this drone into a suitcase full of heavy shoes and other items for a trip from Virginia to Turkey. The suitcase was handled roughly, and the boxes inside were damaged—including the drone's box—but when I unpacked everything, the drone was completely unscathed. The build quality is just that good! Here’s something insane to think about: imagine there’s an island on the Chesapeake Bay you want to fly over. It’s 7 km away, and this drone has a 10 km range without any signal extenders. But here’s the catch—your drone isn’t fully charged. You figure it’s fine and put the drone in sport mode to help it get there faster. But you completely underestimate how long the charge will last (which, by the way, is super long with this amazing piece of tech). When you’re 4 km out, the drone warns you that it doesn’t have enough charge to go much further and return safely. If you don’t listen, it’ll automatically turn back on its own. It’s like this drone is designed to be unbreakable and impossible to lose! Oh, and did I mention it can even handle CRAZY winds? This thing is a total beast. Last thing: I recommend buying an extra 2 chargers and charging station. Instead of getting 31 mins of flight time, you can get 1.5 hours of it with three batteries. It makes a big difference. Long story short, if you’re on the fence, don’t be. Just buy it—you won’t regret it. Read more

original_review.review_title: Very good big, comfortable, stylish bag. But be wary about overfilling
original_review.review_text: I needed a big large bag to hold my Magic the Gathering collection of binders and decks.  This bag satisfied my needs and I am overall very happy with it and would recommend to others for any storage/travel needs. This bag is very large and comfortable. It offers lots of storage space with some neat and fun features as well. It comes in good colors and I love the leather bottom, very similar to Jansport backpacks. All that said, the items that I keep in this bag are very heavy.  This is a bit hard to explain, but when I wear it I feel so much tension/pulling on the stitching where the shoulder straps meet the top of the backpack, I worry that some time sooner than later, the stitching there will fail. At this moment, that is just speculation.  If that ever happens I will come back to this review and update with when I bought it and when it broke. In the meantime, I would recommend this back to most anyone. Just keep in mind though how much you're putting in the bag, it is very large and you could be overfilling before you know it. Read more

sentences[5]: All that said, the items that I keep in this bag are very heavy.

original_review.review_title: Excellent for casual video and general use
original_review.review_text: I mainly use my 13" MacBook Pro for music production, programming, and then some general web browsing, writing, and real casual general computer work. I'm not a gamer so I don't need 120Hz refresh rates. All I needed was something that would be easy on my eyes, look good in my space, and have a nice crisp display. This monitor is simple to set up. It's got 3 screws. You can move it side to side but there's only 20 degrees of vertical movement. That's fine if you want to look at your monitor head-on or angled slightly up at you but if you need something that tilts downward you'll have to get a VESA mount that either clamps to your desk or mounts to your wall. 22 inches is plenty big with an HD screen and just what I needed when in a dual or triple monitor situation (occasionally I use my work-provided monitor in a 3 monitor setup). For music production it doesn't strain your eyes to be staring at it for hours on end. Same when you're programming. Any monitor will give you eye strain eventually but this one is not going to give most people any issues most of the time. You have  options for HDMI or VGA connections. In my case I had to use a VGA cable for my work monitor in the past so I got an adapter for my laptop for USB-C to VGA connections. This works fine and the quality is the same as HDMI with this particular monitor because VGA quality goes up to around a thousand more pixels than 1080p and supports a refresh rate of 85Hz (assuming you didn't get a cheap cable). This monitor has a 75Hz refresh rate so using a VGA connection is not going to reduce quality. In fact I suspect that they chose HDMI and VGA precisely because the monitor works within the VGA spec and HDMI is just a very common connector these days so they included both while excluding DisplayPort because that's mainly used for higher spec machines and people shopping for a budget monitor likely wouldn't have a DisplayPort compatible computer. Plus DP is not super common anyway outside of offices and expensive computers and has little practical benefits over HDMI to the average person right now. But don't let the fact that this is a budget monitor fool you. If you know you need higher refresh rates because you'll be watching movies and gaming then sure, this isn't for you. If you know you're going to be doing work, browsing the web, watching YouTube videos, coding, doing regular boring average computer stuff, then this is going to be more than enough for you. This is the monitor that should be the default standard for everyone looking for an external laptop monitor or that would come with any PC bundle. I wouldn't want lower quality and most wouldn't even notice higher specs if it had them. It's in the perfect spot. If you need an excellent monitor that isn't a thousand dollar  gaming monitor that's basically a flat screen TV made for the Super Bowl then this will be as good as any other. Read more

original_review.review_text: Eerst was ik van plan om een drone van van het duurdere model onder de 250 g te kopen. Toen dacht ik van laat ik eerst eens kijken of deze hobby wat voor mij is door deze budget drone te kopen. Het is een hele leuke kennismaking gebleken. Wat ik niet meer doe is amazons keuze volgen want achteraf had ik liever het combinatiepakket gekocht met extra batterijen met tas + lader en alle extra's die bij het Combo more pakket inbegrepen zijn. Nu moet ik al deze artikelen los bijkopen en dan ben je zoveel duurder uit dat je gelijk wel een duurder model drone had kunnen kopen. Ik snap Amazon wel dat er zo meer te verdienen valt met deze handreiking naar de verkoper. Deze les kost mij veel extra geld omdat ik alles nu los moet aanschaffen. Uiteraard koop ik deze extra's niet bij Amazon maar bij een webshop eindigend met Express. Mijn aanbeveling voor andere verkopers ga altijd voor het Combo pakket of koop gelijk een duurdere drone. Read more

original_review.review_text: Excelente monitor, no podría recomendarlo para gaming puesto que la respuesta de frecuencia no es alta, pero lo recomiendo para trabajos de producción en donde se necesite una calibración adecuada de los colores. El diseño es elegante y delgado, tiene un aspecto profesional... Yo lo recomiendo para creadores de contenido o trabajos con programas de edición de fotografías y video, dadas las dimensiones es ideal para este tipo de trabajo y te permite calibrar los colores de forma "plana" Read more
